### ============================================================
### 🎤 Demos — Walkthrough in talk order
### ============================================================
### This file mirrors the demo flow of the talk and the
### slides in /presentation. Run requests top-to-bottom during the
### talk. Each section is labelled with the slide / chapter it backs.
###
### Setup once before the talk:
###   ./generate-jwt.sh ORGANIZER   → paste into http-client.env.json as jwt_organizer
###   ./generate-jwt.sh ATTENDEE    → paste as jwt_attendee
###   ./generate-jwt.sh SPEAKER     → paste as jwt_speaker
###   docker compose up -d          → starts Jaeger on http://localhost:16686
### ============================================================


### ============================================================
### 0. Intro — show the running app (slide 01)
### ============================================================

### "Same WAR, no runtime-specific code"
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Accept: application/json


### ============================================================
### 0.5 API Model ≠ Domain Model (slide 01d)
### ============================================================
### Same domain, two API shapes. Show v1 (flat) vs v2 (enriched).

### V1 — flat DTO with foreign-key IDs
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Accept: application/json

### V2 — enriched DTO with embedded speaker + room
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v2/sessions
Accept: application/json


### ============================================================
### Ch1. The Gatekeepers — sanitization & validation (slides 02–04b)
### ============================================================

### Demo 1 — HTML/script tags in BODY get stripped (ReaderInterceptor)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "Safe Session <script>alert('xss')</script>",
  "abstract": "Clean abstract <b>bold</b> text.",
  "level": "INTERMEDIATE",
  "track": "Security",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T11:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}

### Demo 2 — HTML in QUERY PARAMS gets stripped (@PreMatching filter)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions?track=<script>alert(1)</script>Cloud
Accept: application/json

### Demo 3 — Bean Validation: empty title + bad duration → 400 with violations[]
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "",
  "level": "BEGINNER",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "durationMinutes": 5
}

### Demo 4 — Custom @NoProfanity validator rejects "phishing"
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "Learn about phishing attacks",
  "abstract": "This title contains a blocked word.",
  "level": "BEGINNER",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T11:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}

### Demo 5 — Audit filter (@Audited) fires here; check server logs for
### "[AUDIT] method=POST uri=... caller=organizer status=201 elapsedMs=..."
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "Audited Session Creation",
  "abstract": "Watch the audit log for this one.",
  "level": "INTERMEDIATE",
  "track": "Observability",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T13:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}


### ============================================================
### Ch2. The Security Shield — JWT + RBAC (slides 05–07)
### ============================================================

### Demo 1 — No token → 401 Problem Details
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Unauthorized Session",
  "abstract": "This should fail.",
  "level": "BEGINNER",
  "track": "Test",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T11:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}

### Demo 2 — ATTENDEE role → 403 Forbidden
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_attendee}}

{
  "title": "Forbidden Session",
  "abstract": "ATTENDEEs cannot create sessions.",
  "level": "BEGINNER",
  "track": "Test",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T11:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}

### Demo 3 — ORGANIZER role → 201 Created 🎉
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "Authorized Session",
  "abstract": "ORGANIZERs can create sessions.",
  "level": "ADVANCED",
  "track": "Security",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "roomId": "room-hall-a",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T14:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}

### Demo 4 — Read endpoints are @PermitAll — no token needed
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Accept: application/json

### Demo 5 — Request Signature (HMAC) → see http/signatures.http
### NOTE: the @SignatureRequired binding is currently not applied to any
### endpoint. To run this demo live, annotate one resource method with
### @SignatureRequired. See signatures.http for details.


### ============================================================
### Ch3. The Lens — Observability (slides 08–10)
### ============================================================

### Demo 1 — Liveness probe (process alive?)
GET http://localhost:8080/health/live
Accept: application/json

### Demo 2 — Readiness probe (data loaded? sessionCount > 0)
GET http://localhost:8080/health/ready
Accept: application/json

### Demo 3 — Combined health (liveness + readiness)
GET http://localhost:8080/health
Accept: application/json

### Demo 4 — Server auto-generates X-Request-Id (check response headers)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Accept: application/json

### Demo 5 — Client-supplied X-Request-Id is preserved (check it echoes back)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Accept: application/json
X-Request-Id: demo-correlation-12345

### Demo 6 — Tracing: make a few calls, then open Jaeger:
###   http://localhost:16686  → service: confapi
###   Look for span attributes: api.version, resource.id, enduser.id, x-request-id
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v2/sessions/sess-cloud-native-java
Accept: application/json
X-Request-Id: trace-demo-1


### ============================================================
### Ch4. The Living Contract — OpenAPI (slides 11–12b)
### ============================================================

### Demo 1 — Generated OpenAPI doc (YAML)
GET http://localhost:8080/openapi
Accept: application/yaml

### Demo 2 — Same doc as JSON
GET http://localhost:8080/openapi
Accept: application/json

### Demo 3 — OASFilter effect: every operation has a 500 response and
### every response has the X-Request-Id header (see ConferenceOASFilter.java).
### Search the YAML output of demo 1 for "X-Request-Id" and "500".


### ============================================================
### Ch5. The Evolution — API Versioning (slides 13–14b)
### ============================================================

### Demo 1 — URI versioning: V1 (flat)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Accept: application/json

### Demo 2 — URI versioning: V2 (enriched, embedded speaker/room)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v2/sessions
Accept: application/json

### Demo 3 — Header versioning: X-API-Version routes /api/sessions → V2
GET http://localhost:8080/api/sessions
Accept: application/json
X-API-Version: 2

### Demo 4 — Header versioning: X-API-Version → V1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/sessions
Accept: application/json
X-API-Version: 1

### Demo 5 — Accept-header parameter versioning
GET http://localhost:8080/api/sessions
Accept: application/json; version=2


### ============================================================
### Ch6. Sane Error Handling — RFC 9457 (slides 15–16)
### ============================================================

### Demo 1 — 404 Problem Details
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions/does-not-exist
Accept: application/json

### Demo 2 — 400 Problem Details with violations[]
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "",
  "level": "BEGINNER",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "durationMinutes": 5
}

### Demo 3 — 401 Problem Details with WWW-Authenticate header
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "No token",
  "level": "BEGINNER",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T11:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}

### Demo 4 — 403 Problem Details (wrong role)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions/sess-cloud-native-java
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_attendee}}

### Demo 5 — Content-Type is application/problem+json — clients can detect errors
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions/does-not-exist
Accept: application/problem+json

